docs.lead_paragraph: THE 1969 Oscar nominations are out and look, at first glance, like an improvement over past years. But, upon slightly closer scrutiny, what might be called the Third Law of Thermodynamics becomes manifest: plus ca change, plus c'est la meme chose, or, in English, there are no changes, only changes rung on the old tunes.
